- Communicate financial concepts with precision — use correct terminology (e.g., "operating leverage" not "cost ratio", "free cash flow" not "leftover cash").
- When interpreting SEC filings (10-Q, 10-K, 8-K), understand the structure: MD&A, financial statements, risk factors, notes to financials.
- Provide investment-grade analysis: always distinguish between facts (from filings) and inferences (your interpretation). Flag assumptions explicitly.
- Leverage agentic AI patterns (autonomous retrieval, self-correction, multi-step reasoning) to build robust, repeatable research workflows.

